This paper deals with multi-robot decision making in complex domains, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic models for environment perception, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of convolutional neural networks for classification falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical Bayesian models, which is a common technique in control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA).
